he agency’s review of the application which could take more than a yeartobacco companies cannot make healthrelated claims about their products in the us without fda authorizationunder a  federal law that gave the fda authority to regulate tobacco products companies can apply to the agency to market novel products as “modified risk” if they might be less hazardous to health the fda has not yet authorized any products as modified riskphilip morris international which has its operational headquarters in lausanne switzerland could sell the iqos product in the united states through altria without making health claims but it would still need to apply to the fda to do so and undergo a separate approval process from the modifiedrisk applicationphilip morris international was spun off as a separate company from altria group in  with altria retaining rights to the us market and philip morris international taking control of business in international marketssome analysts have speculated that the two companies might reunite given consolidation in the global tobacco industrygetting a green light to sell the iqos product in the united states could be a catalyst for the companies to merge tobacco industry analyst bonnie herzog of wells fargo securities wrote in a note to investors on tuesday“given the companies’ history together and close working relationship now on iqos we continue to believe a reunification of philip morris international and altria makes sense” herzog saidshe estimated that  to  percent of the us combustible cigarette market could be converted to iqos by  philip morris international said it expects the fda will take at least  days to complete an administrative review of the application then the agency could take a year to make a final decision on whether to authorize the product as modified riskphilip morris international already sells the iqos product without reduced harm claims in japan italy and switzerland and in some cities in the united kingdom germany denmark portugal russia and ukrainemore than  million smokers have switched to iqos since it first went on sale in  bloomberg news reported demand has proved strongest so far in japan where the product has taken  percent of the markettobacco companies have been experimenting with novel products and diversifying into smokeless tobacco and electronic “vapor” cigarettes as consumption of conventional cigarettes has declined but the industry is divided on what alternative products might become most successfulphilip morris international chief executive officer andre calantzopoulos has said his company may one day stop making traditional cigarettes as the market for alternative products takes hold jblackwelltimesdispatchcom  tags philip morris international commerce economics product john reid blackwell follow john reid blackwell close get email notifications on john reid blackwell daily your notification has been saved there was a problem saving your notification whenever john reid blackwell posts new content youll get an email delivered to your inbox with a link email notifications are only sent once a day and only if there are new matching items save manage followed notifications follow john reid blackwell close followed notifications please log in to use this feature log in dont have an account sign up today most popular in this section grocery chain lidl opens four richmondarea stores more locations planned for region lidl to open four richmondarea stores thursday morning the nowclosed  club in church hill might be turned into luxury apartments new ceo named at henricobased partnermd publix store at john rolfe commons opening in august richmond packaging firm temperpack completes  million investment raise opening second plant in las vegas lighthouse labs names six startups for fall class judge in richmond denies krogers request for injunction against lidl in trademark dispute markel ventures adding large house and garden plant business to its portfolio markel corp plans 